This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language generation and incorporating prior knowledge into the model's output. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new algorithmic framework for training generative models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with natural language processing and dialogue systems. It could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural networks for training the model. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it mentions image captioning as one of the applications of incorporating prior knowledge into the model's output.
